<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the constant.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Specifically, &#91;inf, -inf&#93; represents an empty set.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 Bounds are inclusive.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 -0 is considered to be less than 0 That is, range &#91;0, 0&#93; doesn&#39;t contain</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 3 Currently wrapping ranges are not supported.</span></CodeLine>
